# BitMart Go SDK - Unit Test Credentials Template
#
# Usage: copy this file to .env (same directory) and fill in your real API credentials.
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# Notes:
#   - .env is ONLY used by the unit tests (read by GetDefaultConfig in
#     cloud_client_test.go). It does not affect the SDK library itself.
#   - .env is git-ignored — never commit it.
#   - If .env is missing or a value is left blank, the tests fall back to the
#     placeholder credentials: public (NONE) endpoints still work, while SIGNED
#     endpoints return an authentication error.

BITMART_API_KEY=Your API KEY
BITMART_SECRET_KEY=Your Secret KEY
BITMART_MEMO=Your Memo

# REST base URL (optional). When set, it overrides the base URL for BOTH the
# spot and futures test clients. When unset (or blank), each client falls back
# to its own default constant:
#   spot    -> API_URL_PRO    (https://api-cloud.bitmart.com)
#   futures -> API_URL_V2_PRO (https://api-cloud-v2.bitmart.com)
BITMART_API_URL=https://api-cloud.bitmart.com
